span.strong: This is a reminder that due to the Easter holiday there will be no sack lunches available this Friday, April 10th or next Monday, April 13th. Elementary packets for week 4 may also be picked up on Tuesday, April 14th from 10:00 until 2:00 PM due to the holiday.

span.span: This is a message from the Winner School District regarding the COVID-19 situation. There will be no on-campus instruction at the Winner School District for all grade levels for the remainder of the 2019-20 school year. Students in grades Begindergarten through grade 5 will pick up learning packets each Monday at the Elementary front entry from 10:00 am – 2:00 pm. These learning packets will also be available by clicking the link below. For students in grades 6-12, staff will use Google Classroom to deliver coursework to the students. There will also be no parent-teacher conferences this spring.

Sack lunches will continue to be available for pickup with a drive-thru format in front of the Winner National Guard Armory for all children in our school district from ages 0-18 from Monday through Friday from 12:00pm – 1:00pm until regular school resumes. Effective Monday, March 30th a waiver has been approved by the Department of Agriculture allowing parents to pick up a lunch for their children and the children do not need to be in the vehicle. Lunch will continue to be delivered to the Winner and Ideal communities.
We have set up a Facebook page to post more regular updates.
